# C# language subset (Unity parity)

Synced `src/` must compile in **griddungeon-game** (Unity 6, C# 9). Keep this mirror on the same subset even when `dotnet build` allows newer syntax.

**Authority:** [Unity 6 C# compiler](https://docs.unity3d.com/6000.4/Documentation/Manual/csharp-compiler.html)

## Never use `init` accessors

Unity fails with `CS0518` without `IsExternalInit`. Use `{ get; set; }`, constructor, or factory.

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
public bool ShowCombatAction { get; init; }

// ✅ GOOD
public bool ShowCombatAction { get; set; }
```

## Avoid in `src/`

| Feature | Use instead |
|---|---|
| `record` / `record struct` | `sealed class` / `struct` DTOs |
| `required` members | Constructor validation |
| File-scoped namespaces | Block `namespace { }` |
| C# 10+ features in synced code | C# 9 equivalents |

## DTOs

```csharp
public sealed class ProtocolResolveResult
{
    public IReadOnlyList<CombatActionResult> TargetResults { get; set; } =
        Array.Empty<CombatActionResult>();
}
```

## Nullable

Nullable reference types enabled (`Directory.Build.props`). Match game repo annotations.

